<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call strcmp(username, entry->username) reads both arguments until a '\0' is found but the code does not guarantee that the "username" pointer refers to a NUL‑terminated buffer or that it is non‑NULL. If username (e.g. coming from username_info->username parsed from external input) is not NUL‑terminated or points to a shorter buffer, strcmp will read past the object bounds and thus access out‑of‑bounds memory. This is a direct violation of MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17. (Also calling strcmp with a NULL pointer would be undefined.)
</scenario>
